meta {
  name: Delete Node
  type: http
  seq: 4
}

delete {
  url: {{host}}/agent-playground/graphs/:graph_id/versions/:version_id/nodes/:node_id/
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

params:path {
  graph_id: {{graph_id}}
  version_id: {{version_id}}
  node_id: {{node_id}}
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

vars:pre-request {
  node_id: 52fbb228-5e25-49bb-a001-7e858fb57576
  graph_id: 109ec4c4-37ba-4fdb-8c5a-d59a4e984b12
  version_id: 83159241-8d49-450c-8fd0-870beb9430a4
}

docs {
  # Delete Node

  Soft-delete a node and cascade to its ports, edges, and node connections.

  ## Path Parameters
  - `graph_id` (required): UUID of the graph
  - `version_id` (required): UUID of the draft version
  - `node_id` (required): UUID of the node

  ## Cascade order
  1. All edges connected to the node's ports
  2. All NodeConnections where this node is source or target
  3. All ports on this node
  4. The PromptTemplateNode link (if exists)
  5. The node itself

  ## Response (200)
  ```json
  {
    "status": true,
    "result": {"message": "Node deleted successfully"}
  }
  ```

  ## Side Effects
  - Dataset columns are synced (add-only) after node deletion. Columns are never deleted — they remain in the dataset for other versions that may still reference them.

  ## Errors
  - `400`: Version is not DRAFT
  - `404`: Node not found or doesn't belong to this version
}
